==English==

===Etymology===
From the Old French ''[[ma]] [[dame]]'' (''my lady''), ''[[ma]]'' from the Latin ''[[mea]]'' (feminine form of ''[[meus]]'', ''my''), ''[[dame]]'' from the Latin ''[[dama]]'' (''lady'', ''woman'').

===Noun===
[[Category:English irregular plurals]]
{{en-noun|mesdames}}

# A [[polite]] form of [[address]] for a [[woman]].
# The [[mistress]] of a [[household]].
#{{colloquial}} A [[conceited]] or [[quarrelsome]] [[girl]].
#:''Get to your room, madam!''
#{{slang}} A [[woman]] who runs a [[brothel]].

